#################################################################
# WARNING: !!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!
##################################################################

This shell is compiled using the version 4.0 release 2 of HDF,
and its given libraries.

The software has been tested on SGI and SUN Solaris.  If you are 
using any other operating system, please use at your own risk.

##################################################################
# NOTE: !!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!
##################################################################

This directory contains the files and calls necessary to build the 
NSCAT shell library. This library needs to be build before you
can compile and run any of the readers

Please check the ftp site for update software and makefile versions.

To Come:
	 Makefile for HP
         Makefile for OS
    
         Straight HDF readers (without need to use the nscatshell.a 
	 library both in C and FORTRAN.

##################################################################
# READ: !!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!
##################################################################

1.	You must have a version 4.0 release 2 of HDF installed in
	a know directory in order to be able to run this programs

	You need to be able to run ansi C

2.	This directory contains the following:

		file		README
		file		Makefile.###
		file		fnscat.c
		file		hdfshell.c
		file		hdfshell.h
		file		nscatff.f
		file		testc.c
		file		testc1.c
		file		testf.f
		directory	lib	
			(this directory contains the library nscatshell.a)

3.	Do not edit this Makefile.  This Makefile is design to
	work together with the makefile Makefile.### (where
	### is sgi or solaris) in the main directory.  If you will like
	to compile this directory alone, you will have to
	write your own makefiles to do so.

4.	This directory will be compiled automatically when you
	compile the main directory.  The nscatshell.a library
	will be created during compile.
		
